  "texts": [
    "Each slide bar shows three line indicators: a white line representing the average admission probability of all applicants, a green line showing the initial predictions made by humans/AI, and a yellow line denoting the updated prediction by humans/AI (only shown after an update is made).-The bottom part of this region enables both humans and AI to express opinions on each decision dimension (i.e., applicant attribute).",
    "A simplified profile in the middle (Figure5-5) reduces attention shifts.",
    "Status indicators show if a dimension has been discussed (green), is being discussed (orange), or is yet to be discussed (gray).",
    "Separate \"concrete opinion\" sliders (Figure 5-4 and Figure 5-6) allow AI and humans to share dimension-level opinions.",
    "-Each dimension's slide bar starts in a central position (0% contribution)."
  ],
